summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of car owners' attitudes, specifically focusing on four distinct viewpoints: intolerance of untidiness, keeping up with technology, judging people by their car, and viewing a car solely as transportation. The percentages indicate the proportion of owners of specific car models (Rover, Escort, Sierra, Cavalier) who agree with each statement. Across all surveyed car models, there is a general trend: a higher percentage of owners express agreement with the idea that "A car is only to get from A to B" and "I cannot bear untidiness," with averages of 18% for both. Conversely, fewer owners agree with "I keep up with technology" (average 10%) and "I judge people by the car they drive" (average 2%). The data highlights variations in these attitudes across different car brands, suggesting potential correlations between vehicle ownership and personal philosophies.
